{
  "stem": "10.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I have proof.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have the records here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were again, transported to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was-- came true already.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was the worst camp of all camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were put on the-- on the train, and we traveling.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I looked through the window, and all the stations we are passing are looking familiar to me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we come closer and closer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we stopped even in my hometown, in Katowice.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But they didn't let us out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Another hour, 3/4 of an hour to an hour, I look up-- Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "First of all, I never knew that Oswiecim-- the Polish name-- was changed to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I-- we never knew, in three years-- we are two year-- yeah-- three years being in other camps, that there is a camp in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because we didn't have no communications.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We were entirely separated from the world.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We didn't know from nothing-- and here, Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We got out of the train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We marched a few minutes, because it's right there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's the main camp-- Auschwitz-- and through the gate, and here's a camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The camp was very familiar to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Because since my father's family came from Auschwitz, and we, when we went to school, and my parents went three weeks of summer vacation to resorts in Germany, Czechoslovakia, and Poland, we-- my older brother and myself, we were sent to my grandmother, to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "She lived in Auschwitz yet.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And there, a little city, maybe of 10,000 to 12,000 population, not more, there were more than 90% Jewish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But I remember very well that, naturally, the non-Jews were the mayor, and the police, and-- and the-- the employees in the city.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But otherwise, there were no other non-Jews, only the Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a very commercial city.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
